<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,438,1225]" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1164,1189]" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">Comments:</emphasis>
This exclusively Nicaraguan species is unusual among 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1127,1164,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1127,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="434">Cardiacephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for its overall blue metallic shine and the rounded vertex with a black spot. The narrowed ejaculatory apodeme blade is also unusual.
</paragraph>
